# Reflection

This assignment helped me understand how to transform a basic FastAPI project into a secure backend application. I implemented a user model using SQLAlchemy and validated data using Pydantic schemas.

One of the biggest learning experiences was password hashing and debugging CI/CD issues in GitHub Actions. I also learned how to write unit and integration tests and how automated workflows improve software quality.

Another valuable skill was building Docker images and publishing them to Docker Hub. Overall, this project improved my skills in backend development, testing, deployment, and professional project structure.
